				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$z(\kappa) < z^{'}_{0}$\end{document}z(κ)<z0′, then κ is removed from the solid k-mers and added to the weak k-mers, i.e., improves the purity.

The f0 is the minimum frequency that has been determined, while the z0 and \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
