				\begin{document}$z^{'}_{0}$\end{document}z0′ are learned from the z-score distribution automatically. To obtain the optimal z0, the z-scores of the k-mers having frequency less than f0 are collected. Later, the distribution of these z-scores is estimated and z0 is set as the value having the lowest density between two peaks (viz. the trough of the bimodal; see results for more details). Analogously, \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
